\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 3. C. maximum} L.,{\i  Sp. Pl.} 439 (1753). Robust, stoloniferous perennial 20-40 cm, puberulent and glandular above. Leaves 40-80 × 5-15 mm, lanceolate to linear-lanceolate. Flowers 3-13, in dense umbel-like cymes, with minute bracteoles. Petals up to 3 times as long as the sepals, obcordate, with crenate or dentate lobes. Capsule 17-22 × 6-8 mm, straight; teeth revolute. Seeds c. 1·8 mm, obtusely tuberculate.{\i  E. part of arctic Russia}. Rs(N). ({\i N. Asia and North America.})
