\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 4. C. dahuricum} Fischer ex Sprengel,{\i  Pugillus}{\b  2}: 65 (1815). Glaucous perennial 50-100 cm. Leaves usually 50-80 × 15-30 mm, ovate, subobtuse. Flowers 11-17, in a large, spreading cyme; bracts herbaceous. Sepals 8-12 mm; petals up to twice as long as the sepals, ciliate. Capsule 10-15 mm, straight. Seeds c. 1·5 mm, acutely tuberculate.{\i  Meadows and woodland-margins. E. Russia southwards to} 52°{\i  N}. Rs(N, C).
