\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 5. C. nemorale} Bieb., {\i Fl. Taur.-Cauc.}{\b  3:} 317 (1819). Annual with weak, ascending stems (8-)15-60 cm, hairy. Leaves 20-70 × 3-20 mm, the basal obovate-spathulate, the cauline lanceolate, acute, weakly cordate at the base; all more or less hairy. Inflorescence furcate, many-flowered; pedicels hairy, 1-4 times as long as the sepals. Sepals 6-10 mm, lanceolate, acute, narrowly scarious at the apex, with dense eglandular hairs, without glandular hairs; petals bifid for 1/3 their length, equalling or a little shorter than the sepals, with a ciliate claw; stamens hairy at the base; styles 5. Capsule twice as long as the sepals, more or less bent; teeth deflexed. Seeds 0·7 mm, reddish-brown, tuberculate.{\i  S. & E. Ukraine; Moldavia.} Rs(W, K, E).
