\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 6. C. perfoliatum} L., {\i Sp. Pl.} 437 (1753). Glaucous, glabrous annual up to 50 cm. Leaves up to 40 mm, very narrowly elliptical to ovate-lanceolate, subacute, connate at the base. Inflorescence furcate, with a dichasium of 2-7 flowers at the end of each branch; pedicels 1-2 times as long as the sepals; bracts herbaceous. Sepals 9-11 mm, lanceolate, acute, with a scarious margin at the apex; petals shorter than the sepals, bifid at the apex. Capsule twice as long as the sepals, bent near the apex; teeth deflexed. Seeds 1·2-1·5 mm, acutely tuberculate. 2n = c. 37.{\i  Black Sea region; E. & C. Spain.} Bu Hs Rs(W, K, E), Tu.
