\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 7. C. dichotomum} L., {\i Sp. Pl.} 438 (1753). Annual up to 18 cm; stems densely viscid-glandular. Leaves up to 22 mm, more or less linear, the upper sometimes ovate-lanceolate, densely viscid-glandular. Pedicels shorter than the sepals; bracts herbaceous. Sepals 9-12 mm, more or less lanceolate, acute, densely viscid-glandular, without eglandular hairs; petals c. ½ as long as the sepals, shortly bifid; stamens 5. Capsule 15-22 mm. Seeds 1 mm, chestnut-brown, tuberculate.{\i  Spain; S. Greece}. Gr Hs.
