\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 9. C. grandiflorum} Waldst. & Kit.,{\i  Pl. Rar. Hung.}{\b  2:} 183 (1804) ({\i C. nodosum} Buschm.). Perennial 15-30 cm, caespitose, white- to greyish-tomentose; uppermost internode up to 15 cm. Leaves 25-70 × 0·5-1·5 mm, narrowly linear, subacute, the margins strongly revolute. Inflorescence a fastigiate cyme of 7-15 flowers; peduncles 1-4 cm; bracts ovate to broadly lanceolate, with wide, scarious margins and apices. Sepals 6-8 mm, subobtuse, tomentose, with scarious margins; petals up to 18 mm, gradually tapering towards the base; ovary and capsule tomentose, at least at the base. Capsule straight, up to twice as long as the calyx; teeth flat, patent.{\i  Mountain rocks. • W. Jugoslavia, Albania}. Al Ju.
