\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 10. C. candidissimum} Corr.,{\i  Österr. Bot. Zeitschr.}{\b  59:} 171 (1909) ({\i C. tomentosum} sensu Boiss., non L.,{\i  C. tomentosum} sensu Halácsy, non L.). Perennial 15-30 cm, caespitose, white- to yellowish-lanate; uppermost internode not considerably longer than the others. Leaves c. 20 × 3 mm, lanceolate to linear-lanceolate, subobtuse, straight to curved, the margins revolute. Inflorescence a dense cyme with peduncles and pedicels not more than twice as long as the sepals; bracts ovate, acute to subobtuse, with wide scarious margins. Sepals 5-6 mm, obtuse, white-tomentose; petals up to 10 mm, truncate to auriculate; ovary glabrous. Capsule-teeth flat, recurved . 2n = 36 .{\i  Mountain rocks and screes.•  C. & S. Greece}. Gr.
